ADAM B. SCHIFF, Democrat, of Burbank, CA; born in Framingham, MA,
June 22, 1960; education: B.A., Stanford University, Stanford, CA, 1982; 
J.D., Harvard University, Cambridge, MA, 1985; professional: attorney; 
U.S. Attorney's Office, served as a criminal prosecutor; public service: 
elected to the California State Senate, 1996; involved in numerous 
community service activities; family: married, Eve; children: Alexa and 
Elijah; committees: chair, Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence; 
elected to the 107th Congress on November 7, 2000; reelected to each 
succeeding Congress.

MICHELLE STEEL, Republican, of Orange County, CA; born in Seoul,
South Korea, June 21, 1955; education: B.B.S., Pepperdine University, 
Malibu, CA; M.B.A., University of Southern California, Los Angeles, CA, 
2010; professional: business professional; member, California State 
Board of Equalization, 2007-15; member, 2015-17, chair, 2017-20, Orange 
