professional: lawyer, private practice (business and real estate); 
Colorado State House of Representatives, 1995-98; Colorado State Senate, 
1998-2006; married: Jeanie; children: five; committees: Armed Services; 
Natural Resources; elected to the 110th Congress on November 7, 2006; 
reelected to each succeeding Congress.

JOHN B. LARSON, Democrat, of East Hartford, CT; born in Hartford,
July 22, 1948; education: Mayberry Elementary School, East Hartford, CT; 
East Hartford High School; B.A., Cen

KAT CAMMACK, Republican, of Gainesville, FL; born in Denver, CO,
February 16, 1988; education: B.A., Metropolitan State University of 
Denver, Denver, CO, 2011; M.S., Naval War College, Newport, RI, 2018; 
