2017, by special election, to fill the vacancy caused by the resignation 
of U.S. Representative Mike Pompeo; reelected to the 116th Congress on 
November 6, 2018; reelected to the 117th Congress on November 3, 2020.

JAMES COMER, Republican, of Tompkinsville, KY; born in Carthage,
TN, August 19, 1972; education: B.S., agriculture, Western Kentucky 
University, Bowling Green, KY, 1993;

CLAY HIGGINS, Republican, of Lafayette, LA; born in New Orleans,
LA, August 24, 1961; education: Covington High School, Covington, LA; 
attended Louisiana State University, Baton Rouge, LA; professional: 
Lafayette City Marshal Deputy; Deputy Sheriff, St. Landry Parish; 
officer, Port Barre Police Department; reserve officer, Opelousas Police 
